text: Enclosure or enclosed may refer to: ==Structures== * Container, device creating a partially or fully enclosed space * Cage, an enclosure often made of mesh, bars or wires, used to confine, contain or protect something or someone * Pasture, land used for grazing ==Related pages== * Oppidum, a large fortified Iron Age settlement * Cloister (from Latin , "enclosure"), a feature running along the walls of buildings forming a quadrangle * *
title: Enclosure
